# Environment Configuration

## Backend URL
Set the backend URL using the VITE_BACKEND_URL environment variable:

```bash
# For development
VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3000

# For production
VITE_BACKEND_URL=https://your-backend-domain.com
```

## Environment Files
- `.env.local` - Local development (not committed to git)
- `.env.production` - Production environment
- `.env.example` - Example configuration (committed to git)

The application will fallback to `http://localhost:3000` if no environment variable is set.
